# Loose Cushion Cut Diamond: Prices, Grades & the Round vs Cushion Reality

A loose cushion cut diamond starts at [$1,891 for a GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). A comparable 1ct round? [$3,230](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090690?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). That's 41% cheaper. Same carat. Same quality. Different shape.

Lab cushions go even further. A [2ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal lab cushion costs $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Two carats. D color. VVS1. Under three grand.

---

**TL;DR**

- **Cushion is 35–45% cheaper than round** at the same carat and grade — that's the Pillow Premium
- **Best natural pick:** [1ct GIA G-VS1 Ideal Cushion — $1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- **Best lab pick:** [2ct IGI D-VVS1 Ideal Cushion — $2,606](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28884982?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- **3ct lab GIA cushion:** [D-VVS1 Ideal — $5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — costs the same as a natural 1ct round

→ **Buy loose before you buy the setting.** The Modified Brilliant Split — crushed ice vs large facets — can only be decided stone-in-hand. Once set, that choice is permanent.

---

## Why Buy a Loose Cushion Cut Diamond?

When you buy loose, you see exactly what you're getting before you commit. You pick the stone. You pick the setting. Two separate decisions.

Pre-set rings bundle everything together. The stone, the setting, and the brand markup all land in one price. You don't know what you paid for what.

Buying loose breaks that apart. You pay the real stone price. Then you choose your setting separately — local jeweler, online, or custom.

For cushion cuts specifically, buying loose matters even more. There are two types of cushion cut. They look completely different in person. And you can only tell the difference stone-in-hand, with a video.

Every certified loose stone comes with a GIA or IGI grading report. That report covers cut, color, clarity, carat weight, fluorescence, and measurements. It stays with the stone forever. When you buy a pre-set ring, that individual certificate often disappears into the ring's paperwork. Verifying anything later becomes hard.

You can also verify the certificate yourself before you buy. Go to the GIA website, enter the report number, and confirm the grade matches what the vendor listed. Takes two minutes. Catches mistakes. This level of transparency is only possible when you buy loose with a proper certificate. Pre-set rings don't usually offer this check.

---

## The Modified Brilliant Split

There are two types of cushion cut loose diamond. Most people don't know this. It matters a lot.

**Cushion Modified Brilliant** — called "crushed ice" — has lots of small facets. When you look into it, you see dozens of tiny flashes everywhere. It looks bright and modern. Almost every GIA cushion on the market today is this type.

**Cushion Brilliant** — the old-mine style — has bigger, chunkier facets. Fewer flashes. Each one larger and bolder. It looks more vintage. More dramatic under a single light.

In photos, both look beautiful. Side by side, loose, in your hand, the difference is obvious. One gives you a sparkling, busy look. The other gives you big, bold pops of light.

Once the stone is set into a ring, that decision is done. You can't change it.

Most buyers end up with cushion modified brilliant without even realizing the other option exists. If you want the vintage look, search specifically for cushion brilliant. If you're happy with the modern crushed-ice sparkle, cushion modified is everywhere and well-priced.

Always ask for an HD video before you buy. Still photos don't show the real difference. Video does.

Here's a practical tip: watch the video under two different lighting conditions. Move it into direct light. Then move it to shade. Cushion modified brilliant looks completely different between the two. Cushion brilliant does too, but differently. The way a stone moves in light tells you more than any certificate number.

