## Loose Cushion Cut Diamond Price by Color Grade

Cushion cuts show color a little differently than rounds. The bigger facets can hold warmth. So an H color cushion might look slightly warmer than an H color round.

G is the right stopping point for most buyers.

| Color Grade | 1ct Price Range | Best Pick |
|---|---|---|
| D | [$4,410–$4,921](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/12473312?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | Investment only |
| E–F | [$2,064–$2,265](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25944037?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | Colorless, best value |
| G | [$1,891–$2,252](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | Sweet spot |
| H–I | Below table threshold | Yellow gold only |

G looks white in any setting. F adds about $150 for no visible difference. D adds $2,500+ for the same. Stop at G.

---

## Loose Cushion Cut Diamond Price by Clarity Grade

Cushion modified brilliant hides inclusions better than round brilliant. All those tiny facets scatter light over the inclusion instead of pointing light straight at it.

This means you can sometimes go lower on clarity with a cushion and still get an eye-clean stone.

- **VVS1–VVS2:** You're paying for the certificate. No visible benefit over VS2.
- **VS1–VS2:** Eye-clean in all lighting. This is my recommended floor.
- **SI1:** Often eye-clean in cushion modified. Always watch the HD video first. Can save $300–$600 at 1ct.
- **SI2:** Too risky at 2ct and above. Skip it unless an expert has reviewed the stone.

---

## The Pillow Premium

This is the number that makes cushion buyers smile:

| Stone | Carat | Color-Clarity | Price |
|---|---|---|---|
| GIA Round Brilliant Excellent | 1ct | G-VS2 | [$3,230](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/29090690?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| GIA Cushion Modified Ideal | 1ct | G-VS1 | [$1,891](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |
| **Savings** | — | — | **$1,339 (41%)** |

Cushion costs 35–45% less than round at the same grade. Every carat weight. Consistent.

What does $1,339 in savings actually get you? A platinum setting. Or you skip up to a 1.5ct cushion for the same price as a 1ct round.

Cushion isn't cheaper because it's worse. It's cheaper because fewer people ask for it. If you love the shape, that gap is pure savings.

Here's another way to use the Pillow Premium: instead of buying a 1ct round, buy a 1.5ct cushion for roughly the same money. Or buy a 1ct cushion and use the $1,339 you saved toward a better setting — platinum instead of white gold, or a pavé band instead of a plain one. The cushion shape gives you options that round buyers don't have at the same budget.

