## Expert Summary

A loose cushion cut diamond starts at [$1,891 for a GIA 1ct G-VS1 Ideal](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/23740863?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). That's 41% less than a 1ct round at the same grade. That gap is real. It's there at 2ct, 3ct, and above.

Lab cushions go further. A [GIA 3ct D-VVS1 lab cushion at $5,962](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/26315453?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs less than many natural 1ct rounds. A [GIA 4ct D-VVS1 lab at $7,412](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/25222994?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs less than a natural 1ct D-VVS1.

The Modified Brilliant Split — crushed ice vs large facets — is the one decision you can only make loose. Make it before the stone is set.

For natural: G-VS1 GIA Ideal is the value target at every size. For lab: IGI D-VVS1 Ideal at 2ct and GIA D-VVS1 Ideal at 3ct+ lead the market. Buy loose. Watch the video. Confirm your L/W ratio. Then set it.

